{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review provision and standard of accessible toilets and fund hoists",
        "additional_details": "I find going out in the community difficult as I am in a wheelchair and have cerebral palsy. Whenever I need to go to the toilet, either the toilets are not functioning or filthy, not built for my needs, or not there altogether. This gives me a great amounts of anxiety, and makes me feel worthless as my basic human needs cannot be met.",
        "background": "Many accessible toilets in local communities do not suit some people\u2019s needs. The Government should fund hoists to be included in all accessible toilets. Additionally, they should review the legislation around accessible toilets. Some recently built accessible toilets are not up to scratch.",
